Colors before serialization are different than after deserialization.

I used the following code:

``` c#
var colorContainer = new ColorContainer
{
    ColorA = Color.Red,
    ColorB = Color.Green,
    ColorC = Color.Pink
};

Console.WriteLine("Before");
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorA);
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorB);
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorC);

var xmlWriterSettings = new XmlWriterSettings() {
    Indent = true
};

using (var xmlWriter = XmlWriter.Create("colors.xml", xmlWriterSettings))
{
    IntermediateSerializer.Serialize<ColorContainer>(xmlWriter, colorContainer, null);
}

using (var xmlReader = XmlReader.Create("colors.xml"))
{
    colorContainer = IntermediateSerializer.Deserialize<ColorContainer>(xmlReader, null);
}

Console.WriteLine("After");
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorA);
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorB);
Console.WriteLine(colorContainer.ColorC);
```

The console output:

```
Before
{R:255 G:0 B:0 A:255}
{R:0 G:128 B:0 A:255}
{R:255 G:192 B:203 A:255}
After
{R:255 G:255 B:0 A:0}
{R:255 G:8 B:0 A:0}
{R:255 G:192 B:203 A:255}
```

The XML:

``` xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<XnaContent xmlns:ColorSerializationTest="ColorSerializationTest">
  <Asset Type="ColorSerializationTest:ColorContainer">
    <ColorA>FFFF00</ColorA>
    <ColorB>FF0800</ColorB>
    <ColorC>FFFFC0CB</ColorC>
  </Asset>
</XnaContent>
```
